l_id per kind' (engine.md:126-127)\",\n      \"PreparedWrite::Node and PreparedWrite::Edge carry no logical_id field (src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:596-612); writer accepts kind+body+source_id only\",\n      \"no restore_provenance column / no restore-aware writer path (engine.md:171-179 / recovery.md:148-151)\",\n      \"latest_state op-store collections are keyed by caller-supplied opaque record_key (src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3415-3427); there is no record_key == logical_id contract today, so recovery.md:110-112 has no concrete cascade target\",\n      \"append_only_log op-store collections have no logical_id index / contract; recovery.md:142-145 requires 'ordered events for the logical_id' but the schema cannot answer that query\"\n    ],\n    \"consequences_for_this_slice\": [\n      \"Engine::purge_logical_id cannot delete canonical rows by logical_id — column does not exist; cascade scope (recovery.md:107-115) is unreachable without inventing semantics (record_key == logical_id, etc.) which the prompt explicitly forbids.\",\n      \"Engine::restore_logical_id cannot replay append_only_log into canonical state — writer has no logical_id input, canonical tables have no logical_id column, no supersession, no restore_provenance.\",\n      \"EngineError variants (NoRestorationSource / ConflictingActiveRow / IncompatibleSchema) could be added as enum entries, but with no emit sites they would be dead code — net-positive LoC for zero behavior, contrary to feedback_reliability_principles.md.\",\n      \"CLI wire-up is downstream of the engine seams and cannot proceed.\"\n    ],\n    \"what_was_NOT_touched\": [\n      \"No schema migration written (step 9+ accretion deferred to HITL).\",\n      \"No PreparedWrite variant change.\",\n      \"No EngineError variant addition.\",\n      \"No facade re-export change.\",\n      \"No CLI dispatcher change.\",\n      \"No new test files.\",\n      \"Tree is clean at 718fabe — same as start of slice.\"\n    ],\n    \"prompt_clauses_invoked\": [\n      \"Scope §2 step 3 implementation note: 'if a schema bump is required, surface as a blocker BEFORE writing the schema migration — confirm with the HITL through the orchestrator log first.'\",\n      \"Discipline: 'If the writer path needs a restore_provenance column and schema bump, surface BEFORE adding migration code. The HITL has not pre-approved a schema bump in this slice.'\",\n      \"Scope §1 latest_state cascade note: 'Confirm exact key shape by reading the writer; if latest_state is keyed differently for some kinds, surface as a blocker — do not invent semantics.'\"\n    ],\n    \"minimum_unblock\": [\n      \"HITL decision on a precursor slice (call it 10b-B-pre) that lands the canonical identity substrate: schema migration adding row_id (TEXT NOT NULL) and logical_id (TEXT NOT NULL) and superseded_at (INTEGER NULL) and restore_provenance (TEXT NULL) to canonical_nodes + canonical_edges, partial unique index on (logical_id, kind) WHERE superseded_at IS NULL, plus PreparedWrite::Node/Edge field additions, plus writer supersession step (engine.md:154-169).\",\n      \"Once that lands, this 10b-B slice is straightforward: cascade by logical_id, replay append_only_log through the standard writer with restore_provenance marked.\",\n      \"Alternative HITL decision: amend the spec so 'logical_id' is defined as the existing canonical row identity (e.g. (kind, write_cursor) tuple, or a normalised source_id-scoped key) — but that would invalidate engine.md § Canonical identity and supersession and recovery.md § Logical-id purge and restore wholesale.\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"next_step_for_orchestrator\": \"HITL: choose between (a) spawn precursor slice 10b-B-pre to land the canonical identity substrate, then re-spawn 10b-B; or (b) amend the engine.md / recovery.md specs to redefine 'logical_id' against existing schema. Until then, 10b-B is unreachable per the prompt's own anti-invention rules.\"\n}\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":185,"cache_read_input_tokens":85050,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":185},"output_tokens":49,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e0d30c0-d2ee-4cef-baf2-390d4427d50f","uuid":"17f56083-4518-480d-b026-dbeb58afcd1a"}
