rate shape (single `fathomdb` crate with criterion benches + sqlite-vec feature). 0.6.0 facade crate is a re-export shell; resurrecting `production_paths` bench is net-new authorship of a benchmark harness against a redesigned engine, not restoration. Violates `feedback_reliability_principles` net-negative-LoC bias and `delete-before-add` discipline — that's a Pack 7 perf-evidence slice, explicitly out-of-scope per prompt header.\",\n      \"option_b_recommendation\": \"Omit rust-benchmarks job entirely from initial workflow landing. Track restoration in ci-deferred.md as Pack 7 dependency.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"B2\",\n      \"item\": \"rust-scale-tests\",\n      \"missing\": \"fathomdb-engine `scale` integration test target\",\n      \"evidence\": {\n        \"engine_tests_dir\": \"src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/ — listed contents have no scale.rs (closest matches: durability_soak.rs, perf_gates.rs, neither is a `scale` test)\",\n        \"pre_0_6_0_invocation\": \"cargo nextest run -p fathomdb --test scale (pre-0.6.0 crate name; renamed to fathomdb-engine in 0.6.0)\"\n      },\n      \"option_a_viable\": false,\n      \"rationale_a_rejected\": \"No scale.rs ever existed in the 0.6.0-rewrite engine substrate; authoring one is Pack 7 territory.\",\n      \"option_b_recommendation\": \"Omit rust-scale-tests; or substitute `durability_soak` if orchestrator wants the slot occupied — though `durability_soak` violates `feedback_reliability_principles` (no soak). Recommend: drop.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"B3\",\n      \"item\": \"rust-tracing-stress\",\n      \"missing\": \"fathomdb-engine `tracing` cargo feature AND `tracing_events` test\",\n      \"evidence\": {\n        \"engine_cargo_toml_features\": \"src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/Cargo.toml has no [features] section at all — `--features tracing` will fail with `Package fathomdb-engine v0.6.0 does not have feature 'tracing'`\",\n        \"tracing_events_test\": \"absent (closest: trace_so