er-connection. Distinct from the §3 do-not-retry `cache_size` global tuning entry.\",\n      \"deferred\": \"G.2 (per-worker prepared-statement cache, sticky-connection revisit of E.1) is still motivated by parse_compile = 22.52% conc, but its ratio is 0.61 (share shrinks under concurrency), so it lowers a CPU floor more than it removes a contention point. Defer until G.4 settles.\"\n    },\n    \"if_revert_or_inconclusive\": {\n      \"recommended_orchestrator_action\": \"Run an independent N=5 confirmation pass on the same commit with the same agent-verify-style guardrails. If the second pass reproduces concurrent_median ~ 161 ms (one stddev above the KEEP threshold), this is genuinely lookaside-improving-allocator-pressure but the F.0 baseline's 11.89 ms stddev was tighter than reality; KEEP on a relaxed 'concurrent_median < baseline AND speedup_median > baseline' rule is defensible (movement direction + ratio floor both pass). If the second pass shows no movement or regression, REVERT and pivot directly to G.4 (private page cache) since allocator-arena is then NOT the rate-limiting residual on this host.\",\n      \"reviewer_specific_notes_for_codex_gpt54_high\": \"Lookaside is not on the §5 do-not-retry list. No public Rust API expansion: only `#[cfg(debug_assertions)] #[doc(hidden)]` test accessors per F.0 reviewer convention, and one debug-only `ReaderRequest` variant. FFI uses `c_int` per `feedback_cross_platform_rust.md`; named symbol `ffi::SQLITE_DBCONFIG_LOOKASIDE` not magic 1001. Ordering rc captured + debug-asserted before any PRAGMA / prepare runs. AC-018 unchanged (still green, drain 95 ms). Same-snapshot cursor contract / AC-021 / AC-022 / AC-059b untouched (no read-path SQL or transaction-shape changes).\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"agent_verify_status\": \"pass\",\n  \"agent_verify_reason\": \"`./scripts/agent-verify.sh` (per F.0 reviewer block #3 — NOT `dev/agent-verify.sh`) returned rc=0 on a clean run. First fmt run flagged a rustfmt-style block-vs-inline struct expansion on the new `LookasideStatus` ReaderRequest variant; fixed by running `cargo fmt --all` and re-running. AC-017 + AC-018 release-profile runs both green prior to the AC-020 capture (AC018_NUMBERS drain_ms=95).\",\n  \"do_not_retry_cross_check\": [\n    {\"item\": \"B.1 runtime sqlite3_config(SQLITE_CONFIG_MULTITHREAD)\",                 \"did_not_re_run\": true, \"evidence\": \"G.1 only adds `sqlite3_db_config(SQLITE_DBCONFIG_LOOKASIDE)` — a per-connection allocator setting. No `sqlite3_config` (capital-C global) calls were added or modified. `git log -p f1e66bc..46e3576 -- src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs` shows no SQLITE_CONFIG_MULTITHREAD touch.\"},\n    {\"item\": \"C.1 compile-time SQLITE_THREADSAFE=2 rebuild\",                          \"did_not_re_run\": true, \"evidence\": \"No libsqlite3-sys / build.rs / Cargo.toml feature changes; canonical SQLite serialized mode unchanged. No reproducible-bin layer touched.\"},\n    {\"item\": \"E.1 read-path prepare_cached on borrow/release pool connections\",      \"did_not_re_run\": true, \"evidence\": \"No prepare_cached changes anywhere in this commit. G.2 (sticky thread-affine prepared cache) is still future-packet.\"},\n    {\"item\": \"Reader cache_size / mmap_size global tuning\",                          \"did_not_re_run\": true, \"evidence\": \"No PRAGMA cache_size / mmap_size production-default changes. Only PRAGMAs touched on reader connections at open are the pre-existing journal_mode=WAL + query_only=ON; nothing added.\"},\n    {\"item\": \"Reader open flags READ_ONLY | NO_MUTEX\",                               \"did_not_re_run\": true, \"evidence\": \"Reader open flags untouched: still `Connection::open(&path)` with default flags. Lookaside is a per-connection allocator setting, not an open-flag bit; the §3 NO_MUTEX entry is unrelated and stays not-retried.\"}\n  ],\n  \"tests_run\": [\n    \"cargo build --tests -p fathomdb-engine — green\",\n    \"cargo test -p fathomdb-engine -